cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design of next-generation networks in dense mobile environments, which involves wireless communication and network programmability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses wireless scheduling and flow splitting, which are related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper proposes programmable flow clustering and set policies for inter-group as well as intra-group wireless scheduling, which can be considered as a control system, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses congestion control, which is related to security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach using an emulation environment, which involves multimedia and computer vision, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
